      "date": "2019-04-03 21:19:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nIf there is a concern about conflict with an unlanded patch that is adding the get_lustre_env call to init_logging(), I believe that git will handle the \"conflict\" when merging patches as long as the two changes are identical.\n\nThat would allow the get_lustre_env call to potentially be added in multiple patches if needed, so we don't need to go around and remove the per-script get_lustre_env calls in a later patch.",
